Diagnosis. Ocularium with all tubercles colored, dorsal scutum area I, II and IV with bright yellow tubercles. Free tergites with one pair of bright yellow tubercles. Lateral margins have tubercles with the same color as dorsal scutum, with a white patch near posterior margin (similar to those of
Q. bimaculata
). Anterior margin tubercles white. Male: distal metatarsus I swollen. Penis with three pairs of MS-E directed ventrally.
